title: Hunter Biden
added: Also during October 2020, a fake "intelligence" document went [[viral phenomenon|viral]] on right-wing Internet sites. The document, which claimed that Hunter Biden had connections with China's Communist Party, was supposedly written by a Swiss security analyst named "Martin Aspen", but Aspen does not exist, and his online profile picture was created by [[artificial intelligence]] software. The fabricated report was shared by [[WorldNetDaily]] and [[ZeroHedge]] as well as [[Newt Gingrich]] and [[QAnon]] influencers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/security/how-fake-persona-laid-groundwork-hunter-biden-conspiracy-deluge-n1245387 |title=How a fake persona laid the groundwork for a Hunter Biden conspiracy deluge |website=[[NBC News]] |date=October 29, 2020 |accessdate=October 29, 2020 |first1=Ben |last1=Collins |first2=Brandy |last2=Zadrozny}}</ref>
